{"TopicId":109282,"ForumId":15,"TopicTitle":"What Causes Naughty VAB Icons?","CreatedByName":"Beale","CreatedById":70533,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-05-14T23:14:37Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Beale","CreatedById":70533,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-05-14T23:14:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI talk of this problem!\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://puu.sh/hNybc/d4cd07ef24.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022d4cd07ef24.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EYou can see the part is not contained within its \u0022tile\u0022 in the VAB and extends to block the tile above.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAny way to fix this?\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMany thanks.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEdit:\u003C/strong\u003E Many apologies, this was supposed to go in the modelling sub-forum.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPerhaps a moderator can move it?\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEdit 2:\u003C/strong\u003E Thanks Anon mod!\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222015-05-14T23:36:59Z\u0022 title=\u002205/14/2015 11:36  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00229 yr\u0022\u003EMay 14, 2015\u003C/time\u003E by Beale\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"lo-fi","CreatedById":111099,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-05-16T12:26:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI think I\u0027ve had that when I\u0027ve forgotten colliders..\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nertea","CreatedById":83952,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-05-16T17:06:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EFor me, skinned meshes.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"lo-fi","CreatedById":111099,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-05-16T18:06:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EAh, skinned mesh always makes them tiny for me\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Beale","CreatedById":70533,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-05-16T21:23:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EThanks for the replies guys, I missed these!\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBut, I found the solution:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe problem was, the model of the arm that unfolded needed to be loaded into Unity already in the correct orientation, rather than rotated once added to the scene. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}